Privacy Policy
Effective Date : June 17, 2018
Your privacy is very important to BBstudio Inc.(“BBstudio”) and BBstudio is committed to protecting the privacy of its users (“users” or “you”). We may also refer to BBstudio as “we” or “us”. This Privacy Policy applies whenever you play our games (the “Game” or “Games”) that are available via the Facebook App Center, Apple App Store, Google Play Store, Amazon App Store, Steam Store, or otherwise access any of our other products, services, content, and/or any domains provided by BBstudio (collectively, together with the Games, the “Service” or “Services”).
The purpose of this Privacy Policy is to explain how BBstudio manages, collects, stores, shares, uses and protects the information you provide in connection with any BBstudio game whenever you play or otherwise access any of our Services. Please read this Privacy Policy before using our Services. By accessing and/or using the Service, you agree to the collection, disclosure, storage and use of your personal information as outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you do not want BBstudio to collect, store, use or share your information in the ways set out in this Privacy Policy, you should not play BBstudio’s games or use our Services.
1
INFORMATION WE COLLECT AND HOW WE COLLECT IT
1.1
Information about you that you share with us directly
When you use our Services (whether through a social network or through BBstudio directly), you may give us information directly and we will store that on our systems and use it for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy.
We may let you create a player profile, separate from your social networking site profile (for example, your Facebook profile), that other BBstudio players can see. Your player profile may include information like:
game username(s)
nationality and/or approximate location information that you provide
details about other BBstudio Games you play
1.2
Information about you that we get from third-party application
(like Facebook)
If you play BBstudio’s games or access any of our other Services on connected third-party applications, including social networks like Facebook, BBstudio may receive certain information about you from the provider of the third-party application. The information we receive depends on the BBstudio game you’re playing, the third-party application, your privacy settings and, if applicable, your friends’ privacy settings on that third-party application.
For example, BBstudio may collect and store some or all of the following information shared by the provider of the connected third-party application:
your first and last name
your profile picture or its URL
your user ID number (like your Facebook ID number), which may be linked to publicly-available information like your name and profile photo;
the user ID number and other public data of your friends
the login e-mail you provided to that third-party application when you registered with it
If you access our Services from a third-party application or connect our Services to a third-party application, you should also read that third-party application’s Terms of Service and Privacy Policy. If you are unclear about what information a third-party application is sharing with us, please go to the third-party application to find out more about their privacy practices.
1.3
Information you generate using our services
When you use our Services, we’ll collect information about the ways in which you use and interact with our Services, such as when and for how long you play our games, game features and other players you interact with, purchases you make, progress or levels you achieve, and other activities.
