The retention period of your information depends on why we collected it and how we use it. We will not retain your personal information for longer than is necessary for our business purposes or for legal requirements.  For instance, we may retain your personal information for a few years after you have closed your account with us or after we have stopped providing Services to you if this is necessary to meet our legal obligations, to exercise, defend or establish legal rights, to meet regulatory requirements, to resolve disputes between users, to prevent fraud, cheating or abuse, or to enforce this Privacy Policy or any other agreements we may have with a user.
